types.name: Payment
types.description:
References to Payments subgraph entities

Permissions:PAYMENTS_READ

fields.name: id
fields.description: Unique ID for the payment.

fields.name: amountMoney
fields.description:
The amount processed for this payment, not including `tipMoney`.

The amount is specified in the smallest denomination of the applicable currency (for example,
US dollar amounts are specified in cents). For more information, see
[Working with Monetary Amounts](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-monetary-amounts).

fields.name: appFeeMoney
fields.description:
The amount the developer is taking as a fee for facilitating the payment on behalf
of the seller. This amount is specified in the smallest denomination of the applicable currency
(for example, US dollar amounts are specified in cents). For more information,
see [Take Payments and Collect Fees](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/payments-api/take-payments-and-collect-fees).

The amount cannot be more than 90% of the `total_money` value.

To set this field, `PAYMENTS_WRITE_ADDITIONAL_RECIPIENTS` OAuth permission is required.
For more information, see [Permissions](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/payments-api/take-payments-and-collect-fees#permissions).

fields.name: applicationDetails
fields.description: Details about the application that took the payment.

fields.name: approvedMoney
fields.description: The initial amount of money approved for this payment.

fields.name: bankAccountDetails
fields.description: Details about a bank account payment. These details are only populated if the `sourceType` is `BANK_ACCOUNT`.

fields.name: billingAddress
fields.description: The buyer's billing address.

fields.name: buyNowPayLaterDetails
fields.description:
Details about a Buy Now Pay Later payment. The details are only populated
if the `source_type` is `BUY_NOW_PAY_LATER`. For more information, see
[Afterpay Payments](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/payments-api/take-payments/afterpay-payments).

fields.name: buyerEmailAddress
fields.description: The buyer's email address.

fields.name: capabilities
fields.description: Actions that can be performed on this payment.

fields.name: cardDetails
fields.description: Details about a card payment. These details are only populated if the `sourceType` is CARD.

fields.name: cashDetails
fields.description: Details about a cash payment. These details are only populated if the `sourceType` is `CASH`.

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description: The timestamp of when the payment was created, in RFC 3339 format.

fields.name: customerId
fields.description:
The [Customer](https://developer.squareup.com/reference/square/payments-api/list-payments#type-customer)
ID of the customer associated with the payment.

fields.name: delayAction
fields.description: The action to be applied to the payment when the `delay_duration` has elapsed.

fields.name: delayDuration
fields.description:
The duration of time after the payment's creation when Square automatically applies the
`delayAction` to the payment. This automatic `delayAction` applies only to payments that
don't reach a terminal state (COMPLETED, CANCELED, or FAILED) before the `delayDuration`
time period.

This field is specified as a time duration, in RFC 3339 format.

Notes:
This feature is only supported for card payments.

Default:

  - Card Present payments: "PT36H" (36 hours) from the creation time.
  - Card Not Present payments: "P7D" (7 days) from the creation time.

fields.name: delayedUntil
fields.description:
The read-only timestamp of when the `delay_action` is automatically applied,
in RFC 3339 format.

Note that this field is calculated by summing the payment's `delay_duration` and `created_at`
fields. The `created_at` field is generated by Square and might not exactly match the
time on your local machine.

fields.name: deviceDetails
fields.description: Details about the device that took the payment.

fields.name: externalDetails
fields.description: Details about an external payment. The details are only populated if the `sourceType` is `EXTERNAL`.

fields.name: locationId
fields.description: The ID of the location associated with the payment.

fields.name: merchantId
fields.description: The ID of the merchant associated with the payment.

fields.name: note
fields.description: An optional note to include when creating a payment.

fields.name: orderId
fields.description: The ID of the order associated with the payment.

fields.name: processingFees
fields.description: The processing fees and fee adjustments assessed by Square for this payment.

fields.name: receiptNumber
fields.description:
The payment's receipt number.
The field will be missing if a payment is canceled.

fields.name: receiptUrl
fields.description:
The URL for the payment's receipt.
The field is only populated for COMPLETED payments.

fields.name: referenceId
fields.description: An optional ID that associates this payment with an entity in another system.

fields.name: refundedMoney
fields.description:
The total amount of the payment refunded to date.

This amount is specified in the smallest denomination of the applicable currency (for example,
US dollar amounts are specified in cents).

fields.name: refunds
fields.description: The refunds for this payment.

fields.name: riskEvaluation
fields.description:
Provides information about the risk associated with this payment, as determined by Square.
This field will be present for payments to sellers that have opted in to receive risk
evaluations.

fields.name: shippingAddress
fields.description: The buyer's shipping address.

fields.name: sourceType
fields.description:
The source type for the payment.

For information about these payment source types,
see [Take Payments](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/payments-api/take-payments).

fields.name: statementDescriptionIdentifier
fields.description:
Additional payment information that gets added on the customer's card statement
as part of the statement description.

Note that the `statementDescriptionIdentifier` may get truncated on the statement description
to fit the required information including the Square identifier (SQ *) and name of the
seller taking the payment.

fields.name: status
fields.description: Indicates whether the payment is APPROVED, PENDING, COMPLETED, CANCELED, or FAILED.

fields.name: teamMemberId
fields.description: An optional ID of the TeamMember associated with taking the payment.

fields.name: tipMoney
fields.description:
The amount designated as a tip.

This amount is specified in the smallest denomination of the applicable currency (for example,
US dollar amounts are specified in cents). For more information, see
[Working with Monetary Amounts](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-monetary-amounts).

fields.name: totalMoney
fields.description:
The total amount for the payment, including `amountMoney` and `tipMoney`.

This amount is specified in the smallest denomination of the applicable currency (for example,
US dollar amounts are specified in cents). For more information, see
[Working with Monetary Amounts](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-monetary-amounts).

fields.name: updatedAt
fields.description: The timestamp of when the payment was last updated, in RFC 3339 format.

fields.name: walletDetails
fields.description: Details about an wallet payment. The details are only populated if the `sourceType` is `WALLET`.

types.name: PaymentApplicationDetails
types.description:
Permissions: PAYMENTS_READ

Details about the application that took the payment.

fields.name: applicationId
fields.description:
The Square ID assigned to the application used to take the payment.
Application developers can use this information to identify payments that
their application processed.
For example, if a developer uses a custom application to process payments,
this field contains the application ID from the Developer Dashboard.
If a seller uses a [Square App Marketplace](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/app-marketplace)
application to process payments, the field contains the corresponding application ID.

fields.name: squareProduct
fields.description: The Square product, such as Square Point of Sale (POS), Square Invoices, or Square Virtual Terminal.

Represents an application processing fee.

fields.description: The exact fee amount assessed based on the payment fee rate.

fields.name: effectiveAt
fields.description: The timestamp of when the fee takes effect, in RFC 3339 format.

fields.name: partyAccountId
fields.description:
The platform account token for this payment fee.
For a capture, this is the recipient of funds. For a refund, this is the source of funds.

fields.name: priceSelectors
fields.description: The price selector IDs of the payment fee being applied.

fields.name: type
fields.description: The type of payment fee being applied (for example, `THIRD_PARTY_PAYMENT_FEE` or `THIRD_PARTY_REFUND_FEE`).

types.name: PaymentAppProcessingFeeFieldsListFilter
types.description:
Input type used to specify filters on a `PaymentAppProcessingFee` object referenced directly
or transitively from a list field that has been configured to index each leaf field as
its own flattened list of values.

Will be ignored if passed as an empty object (or as `null`).

types.description: The type of payment fee being applied.

types.name: PaymentAppProcessingFeeTypeListElementFilter

Input type used to specify filters on elements of a `[PaymentAppProcessingFeeType]` field.

types.name: PaymentAppProcessingFeeTypeListFilter
types.description:
Input type used to specify filters on `[PaymentAppProcessingFeeType]` fields.

Will be ignored if passed as an empty object (or as `null`).

enumValues.description: The payment amount can be edited down.

enumValues.name: EDIT_AMOUNT_UP
enumValues.description: The payment amount can be edited up.

enumValues.name: EDIT_DELAY_ACTION
enumValues.description: The delay action can be edited.

enumValues.name: EDIT_TIP_AMOUNT_DOWN

types.name: PaymentRefund
types.description:
Permissions: PAYMENTS_READ

Represents a refund of a payment made using Square. Contains information about
the original payment and the amount of money refunded.


For more performant queries on this type, please filter on `merchantId` if possible.

fields.name: amountMoney
fields.description:
The amount of money refunded. This amount is specified in the smallest denomination
of the applicable currency (for example, US dollar amounts are specified in cents).

fields.name: appFeeMoney
fields.description:
The amount of money the application developer contributed to help cover the refunded amount.
This amount is specified in the smallest denomination of the applicable currency (for example,
US dollar amounts are specified in cents). For more information, see
[Working with Monetary Amounts](https://developer.squareup.com/docs/build-basics/working-with-monetary-amounts).

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description: The timestamp of when the refund was created, in RFC 3339 format.

fields.name: id
fields.description: The unique ID for this refund, generated by Square.

fields.name: locationId
fields.description: The location ID associated with the payment this refund is attached to.

fields.name: merchantId
fields.description: The merchant ID associated with the payment this refund is attached to.

fields.name: orderId
fields.description: The ID of the order associated with the refund.

fields.name: payment
fields.description: The payment this refund belongs to.

fields.name: paymentId
fields.description: The ID of the payment associated with this refund.

fields.name: processingFees
fields.description: Processing fees and fee adjustments assessed by Square for this refund.

fields.name: reason
fields.description: The reason for the refund.

fields.name: status
fields.description: The refund's status.

fields.name: teamMemberId
fields.description: An optional ID of the team member associated with taking the payment.

fields.name: updatedAt
fields.description: The timestamp of when the refund was last updated, in RFC 3339 format.

types.name: PaymentRiskEvaluation
types.description:
Permissions: PAYMENTS_READ

Represents fraud risk information for the associated payment.

When you take a payment through Square's Payments API (using the `CreatePayment`
endpoint), Square evaluates it and assigns a risk level to the payment. Sellers
can use this information to determine the course of action (for example,
provide the goods/services or refund the payment).

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description: The timestamp when payment risk was evaluated, in RFC3339 format.

fields.name: riskLevel
fields.description: The risk level associated with the payment.

types.name: PaymentRiskEvaluationFilter
types.description:
Input type used to specify filters on `PaymentRiskEvaluation` fields.

Will be ignored if passed as an empty object (or as `null`).

types.name: PaymentRiskEvaluationRiskLevel
types.description: Represents a risk level produced by evaluating a payment.

enumValues.name: HIGH
enumValues.description: Indicates significantly elevated risk level with the payment.

enumValues.name: MODERATE
enumValues.description: Indicates elevated risk level associated with the payment.

enumValues.name: NORMAL
enumValues.description: Indicates payment risk is within the normal range.

enumValues.name: PENDING
enumValues.description: Indicates Square is still evaluating the payment.

types.name: PaymentRiskEvaluationRiskLevelFilter
types.description:
Input type used to specify filters on `PaymentRiskEvaluationRiskLevel` fields.

Will be ignored if passed as an empty object (or as `null`).

types.name: PaymentSortOrder
types.description: Enumerates the ways `Payment`s can be sorted.

types.name: PaymentSourceType
types.description:

enumValues.name: ADDITIVE
enumValues.description:
The tax is an additive tax. The tax amount is added on top of the
CatalogItemVariation price. For example, a $1.00 item with a 10% additive
tax would have a total cost to the buyer of $1.10.

enumValues.name: INCLUSIVE
enumValues.description:
The tax is an inclusive tax. The tax amount is included in the
CatalogItemVariation price. For example, a $1.00 item with a 10% inclusive
tax would have a total cost to the buyer of $1.00, with $0.91 (91 cents) of
that total being the cost of the item and $0.09 (9 cents) being tax.

types.name: __Schema
types.description: A GraphQL Schema defines the capabilities of a GraphQL server. It exposes all available types and directives on the server, as well as the entry points for query, mutation, and subscription operations.

fields.name: types
fields.description: A list of all types supported by this server.

fields.name: queryType
fields.description: The type that query operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: mutationType
fields.description: If this server supports mutation, the type that mutation operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: subscriptionType
fields.description: If this server support subscription, the type that subscription operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: directives
fields.description: A list of all directives supported by this server.

types.name: __Type
types.description:
The fundamental unit of any GraphQL Schema is the type. There are many kinds of types in GraphQL as represented by the `__TypeKind` enum.

Depending on the kind of a type, certain fields describe information about that type. Scalar types provide no information beyond a name, description and optional `specifiedByURL`, while Enum types provide their values. Object and Interface types provide the fields they describe. Abstract types, Union and Interface, provide the Object types possible at runtime. List and NonNull types compose other types.

types.name: __TypeKind
types.description: An enum describing what kind of type a given `__Type` is.

enumValues.name: SCALAR
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a scalar.

enumValues.name: OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an object. `fields` and `interfaces` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: INTERFACE
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an interface. `fields`, `interfaces`, and `possibleTypes` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: UNION
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a union. `possibleTypes` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: ENUM
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an enum. `enumValues` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: INPUT_OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an input object. `inputFields` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: LIST
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a list. `ofType` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: NON_NULL
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a non-null. `ofType` is a valid field.

types.name: __Field
types.description: Object and Interface types are described by a list of Fields, each of which has a name, potentially a list of arguments, and a return type.

types.name: __InputValue
types.description: Arguments provided to Fields or Directives and the input fields of an InputObject are represented as Input Values which describe their type and optionally a default value.

fields.name: defaultValue
fields.description: A GraphQL-formatted string representing the default value for this input value.

types.name: __EnumValue
types.description: One possible value for a given Enum. Enum values are unique values, not a placeholder for a string or numeric value. However an Enum value is returned in a JSON response as a string.

types.name: __Directive
types.description:
A Directive provides a way to describe alternate runtime execution and type validation behavior in a GraphQL document.

In some cases, you need to provide options to alter GraphQL's execution behavior in ways field arguments will not suffice, such as conditionally including or skipping a field. Directives provide this by describing additional information to the executor.

types.name: __DirectiveLocation
types.description: A Directive can be adjacent to many parts of the GraphQL language, a __DirectiveLocation describes one such possible adjacencies.

enumValues.name: QUERY
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a query operation.

enumValues.name: MUTATION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a mutation operation.

enumValues.name: SUBSCRIPTION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a subscription operation.

enumValues.name: FRAGMENT_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a fragment definition.

enumValues.name: FRAGMENT_SPREAD
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a fragment spread.

enumValues.name: INLINE_FRAGMENT
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an inline fragment.

enumValues.name: VARIABLE_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a variable definition.

enumValues.name: SCHEMA
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a schema definition.

enumValues.name: SCALAR
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a scalar definition.

enumValues.name: OBJECT
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an object type definition.

enumValues.name: FIELD_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a field definition.

enumValues.name: ARGUMENT_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an argument definition.

enumValues.name: INTERFACE
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an interface definition.

enumValues.name: UNION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to a union definition.

enumValues.name: ENUM
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an enum definition.

enumValues.name: ENUM_VALUE
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an enum value definition.

enumValues.name: INPUT_OBJECT
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an input object type definition.

enumValues.name: INPUT_FIELD_DEFINITION
enumValues.description: Location adjacent to an input object field definition.
